{"type":"message","id":"1b943a61","parentId":"fe02301b","timestamp":"2026-07-13T07:13:44.764Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d28bba107a2d49769de14b78","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Content Calendar — Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n---\n\n## Scheduled Posts — Benchmark-First AI Agent Series\n\n### Post 1: The anatomy of a good benchmark (July 7, 9:00 AM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** 📅 Scheduled for auto-publish\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗱𝗶𝗳𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘁𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗻 𝗮 𝗵𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗳𝘂𝗹 𝗔𝗜 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗷𝗲𝗰𝘁 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗮 𝘀𝗲𝗹𝗳-𝗲𝘃𝗼𝗹𝘃𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗼𝗻𝗲?\n\nOne has a benchmark. The other has vibes.\n\nA good benchmark answers three questions:\n\n1. **What's the task?** (specific, not vague)\n2. **What does \"done\" look like?** (verifiable outcome)\n3. **How do you measure it?** (quantifiable metric)\n\nMost teams skip this. They build the agent first, then scramble to figure out if it's working.\n\nFlip it. Write the benchmark BEFORE a single line of code. Make it pass. Then make the agent chase it.\n\nThe benchmark IS your reward function. Every iteration moves the needle. Every failure teaches the system.\n\nThis is TDD for AI. Test first. Agent second.\n\nWhat's one AI project you're building without a clear benchmark?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #TDD #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering\n\n**Characters:** ~950\n\n---\n\n### Post 2: Why most AI agents drift (July 7, 3:00 PM UTC)\n\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Key Message:** #4 — Benchmark-first AI Agent development\n**Status:** ✅ Published — https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480274563235254272/\n\n**Draft:**\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗱𝗮𝘆. 𝗜𝘁 𝗯𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗸𝘀 𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗿𝗼𝘄. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗼𝗻'𝘁 𝗸𝗻𝗼𝘄 𝘄𝗵𝘆.\n\nSound familiar?\n\nThis is the drift problem. Most agents have no anchor. They optimize for whatever feels right in the moment — but there's no fixed target.\n\nThe fix: **benchmark + reward function.**\n\nDefine the outcome. Make it measurable. Let the agent optimize toward it.\n\nEvery successful iteration is progress. Every failure is a signal. No guessing.\n\nTraditional software has tests. AI agents need benchmarks.\n\nWithout one, you're not building a system. You're building a feeling.\n\nWhat's your agent's benchmark — or are you hoping it figures itself out?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #MachineLearning #SoftwareEngineering #TDD\n\n**Characters:** ~900\n\n---\n\n## Trend Proposals — 2026-07-03\n\n### Claude Fable 5 outage exposed a fatal gap: only 1 in 10 enterprises can auto-catch failing AI\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-lost-claude-fable-5-for-a-few-weeks-new-data-shows-two-thirds-had-already-built-their-hedge\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\" — You built an AI agent. It went down. Did you even notice? Most teams have no fallback detection. That's the real risk.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗹𝗮𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗲𝗸. 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗱𝗶𝗱𝗻'𝘁 𝗻𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗰𝗲.\n**Persona:** CTO at 200+ person company — running production AI, can't afford silent failures\n**Status:** ✍️ Writing now\n\n---\n\n### Trunk Tools cut document review from 60 days to 10 — by ditching general-purpose models\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/trunk-tools-cut-document-review-from-60-days-to-10-by-ditching-general-purpose-models\n**Published:** July 3, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"The mistake most people will make\" — Most teams throw GPT-4 at everything. The winners are building specialized stacks that skip the bloat.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗼𝗻𝗲 𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹. 𝗜𝘁'𝘀 𝘇𝗲𝗿𝗼 𝗯𝗹𝗼𝗮𝘁.\n**Persona:** CTO at IT consultancy — needs to deliver client projects faster with reusable components\n**Scheduled:** July 7, 2026 (Monday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### DeepSeek open-sourced DSpark — 85% faster LLM inference\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/deepseek-open-sources-dspark-a-new-framework-to-speed-up-llm-inference-by-up-to-85\n**Published:** June 29, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — Inference costs are collapsing. If your AI strategy depends on one provider's pricing, you're overpaying. Open-source is eating the margin.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗜𝗻𝗳𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁 𝘁𝗼 𝗰𝗼𝗹𝗹𝗮𝗽𝘀𝗲.\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — wants AI competitiveness without bleeding budget\n**Scheduled:** July 10, 2026 (Thursday)\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Morgan Stanley made its AI agents LESS autonomous — and cut riskiest job in half\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/morgan-stanley-cut-its-riskiest-reconciliation-job-in-half-by-making-its-agents-less-autonomous\n**Published:** June 30, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"Contrarian take\" — Everyone's chasing fully autonomous agents. Morgan Stanley went the opposite direction — and won. Sometimes constraints beat freedom.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗠𝗼𝗿𝗴𝗮𝗻 𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗻𝗹𝗲𝘆'𝘀 𝗯𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗔𝗜 𝘄𝗶𝗻? 𝗠𝗮𝗸𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗹𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗮𝘂𝘁𝗼𝗻𝗼𝗺𝗼𝘂𝘀.\n**Persona:** Enterprise Innovation Officer at financial services company — zero tolerance for error, needs reliable AI\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n### Restaurants now take orders from ChatGPT and Claude directly — no app, no setup\n**Source:** https://venturebeat.com/technology/restaurants-can-now-accept-orders-placed-directly-from-chatgpt-and-claude-thanks-to-squares-new-low-fee-no-setup-integration\n**Published:** July 1, 2026\n**Pillar:** Technology & AI innovations\n**Angle:** \"What this means for you\" — AI agents are now ordering dinner. Your customers will expect the same from your business. The question isn't if — it's how fast you can plug in.\n**Post hook draft:** 𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗼𝗿𝗱𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗻𝗲𝗿. 𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗲𝘅𝗰𝘂𝘀𝗲?\n**Persona:** Founder/CEO at SMB — needs to stay competitive with AI integration\n**Status:** Proposed 🔎\n\n---\n\n## Published Posts\n\n- 2026-07-06: Test-driven development changed how we write software (TDD ↔ Benchmark for AI Agents)\n- 2026-07-03: Alibaba just cut AI agent token use by 99%\n- 2026-06-25: Most companies are building AI backwards\n- 2026-06-25: AI isn't coming for your job\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783926824757}}
{"type":"message","id":"142346ac","parentId":"1b943a61","timestamp":"2026-07-13T07:13:51.279Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_275e83c9a0974669add8daf2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0b172a6be56e4baf8f11c9b7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/ 2>/dev/null | head -20"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"ls -la /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/ 2>/dev/null | head -20\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783926824790,"responseId":"KZBUauavPMiGkuwP06bUqAY"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3e8392e8","parentId":"142346ac","timestamp":"2026-07-13T07:13:51.359Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_275e83c9a0974669add8daf2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# LinkedIn Brand Voice - Andrii Bidochko\n\n**Owner:** 264468965\n**Last updated:** 2026-07-06\n\n## Identity & Goals\n\n- **Target audience:** Business professionals, entrepreneurs, tech-savvy individuals seeking growth and insights\n- **Primary goal:** Maximum organic engagement (impressions, comments, shares) through thought leadership and value-driven content\n\n## Buyer Personas\n\n*(Who specifically should feel spoken to by every post)*\n\n- **Persona 1:** Enterprise Innovation Officer / CTO at 200+ person company (Financial Services, Healthcare, Retail) - Pain: Needs rapid AI solution development without vendor lock-in or heavy internal R&D\n- **Persona 2:** CTO / Software Architect at 75+ person IT consultancy or agency - Pain: Needs to deliver AI-powered client projects faster with reusable components\n- **Persona 3:** Founder / CEO / Head of Operations at 10-200 person SMB - Pain: Wants automation and AI competitiveness but lacks the engineering resources or budget\n\n## Content Pillars\n\n1. Business & entrepreneurship insights\n2. Technology & AI innovations\n3. Personal development & mindset\n\n## Company / Product Context\n\n- **Company:** UBOS (ubos.tech)\n- **What it does:** AI Agent Orchestration Platform - build, host, and manage AI Agents in minutes using open-source tools (Langchain, CrewAI, Autogen, Vertex AI), 100+ LLM models, one-click cloud/on-premise deployment\n- **Key differentiators:** No vendor lock-in (open-source, multi-cloud), unlimited agents as microservices, works with any LLM including self-hosted (Llama, Deepseek)\n- **Mission:** \"Help people build better software\"\n- **Key messages to reinforce:**\n  1. AI can be affordable and accessible - even for small businesses\n  2. Implementing AI doesn't require a big team or deep tech expertise\n  3. Every company will become AI-first - the question is when, not if\n  4. **Benchmark-first AI Agent development** — The best way to build self-evolving AI agents is to start with a verifiable benchmark and reward function (like TDD for software). Define the outcome BEFORE the agent, then let it optimize toward it.\n\n## Voice & Tone\n\n- **Style:** Gary Vaynerchuk (Gary Vee) - Direct, energetic, bold, motivational, conversational. Short punchy lines, strong opinions, urgency. Powerful language with strong verbs, imperative statements, and intensifiers (\"absolutely,\" \"definitely,\" \"100%\"). Keep it real and direct with colloquial language. Create urgency with \"right now,\" \"immediately.\" Use repetition for emphasis. Casual but pointed tone.\n- **Avoid:** Neutral reporting, corporate/formal tone, vague humble-brags, excessive emojis (max 0-3 per post), generic hashtags (#success, #motivation), salesy CTAs\n\n## Hashtag Strategy\n\n- Always use: 3-6 hashtags placed at the END of the post only\n- Topic-specific: Industry, role, or topic-specific hashtags preferred\n- Never use hashtags inside sentences\n\n## Post Production Rules\n\n*(Apply to EVERY post - non-negotiable)*\n\n### Length & Structure\n- Target: 900-1,300 characters (hard min 800, max 1,400)\n- Max 14 lines total; 1-2 short sentences per line\n- Structure: 1-3 hook lines -> 6-10 body lines -> 1-2 CTA lines\n\n### Hook rules\n- Pattern interrupt - ONE of: contrarian statement, direct challenge, consequence reveal\n- Unicode bold sans for hook line ONLY - no Markdown, no *, no _\n\n### Body rules\n- ONE comment trigger: direct question, A vs B, or unfinished thought\n- Contrast: old belief vs reality, OR short-term comfort vs long-term cost\n- ONE save-worthy insight: a rule, checklist, or named pattern\n- \"you\" and \"your\" throughout; ALL CAPS on 1-2 key words max\n- Speak directly to a buyer persona's pain\n- Gary Vee style ALWAYS takes precedence over any example post tone\n\n### CTA rules\n- Question, never a command; no selling language\n\n### Hashtag rules\n- 3-6 at END only; never inside sentences; prefer industry/role/topic-specific\n- Avoid: #success, #motivation\n\n### Formatting rules\n- NO Markdown; Unicode emphasis on hook/key phrase only, never full paragraphs\n- Emojis: 0-3 max per post\n\n### News framing\n- Reframe using ONE angle: \"What this means for you\" / \"Why this is underestimated\" / \"The mistake most people will make\" / \"The second-order effect nobody mentions\"\n- Never neutral reporting - always add perspective, judgment, or implication\n- If engagement feels weak after drafting - rewrite hook and CTA once before finalizing\n\n## Post Style Guide\n\n- Length: 900-1,300 characters\n- CTA style: question-based\n- Format: calibrate from feedback\n\n## History\n\n- **2026-06-25** | Profile created via detailed configuration import\n- **2026-06-25** | Enriched with Buyer Personas, Company/Product Context (UBOS), consolidated Post Production Rules\n- **2026-07-06** | Added Key Message #4: Benchmark-first AI Agent development (TDD parallel for self-evolving agents)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1783926831355}}
