{"type":"message","id":"b7f9cfea","parentId":"be1afe2e","timestamp":"2026-07-15T00:15:43.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4d55e450175541cabeae6fb2","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗗𝗲𝗲𝗽𝗦𝗲𝗲𝗸 𝗰𝘂𝘁 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲𝘀 𝟳𝟱%. 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘂𝗽.\n\nHere's the math nobody wants to talk about: cheaper tokens don't matter when your agent burns 100x more of them.\n\nA chatbot turns one question into one model call. An agent turns it into planning, retrieval, tool calls, verification, loops. Same user question. 35,000 tokens instead of 200.\n\nThe DeepSeek price cut is real. But token amplification is outrunning the savings. One \"simple\" agent query can cost $0.10-$0.40 on frontier models. A million queries a month? Six figures.\n\nThe vendors winning right now aren't chasing the cheapest model. They're building cost-aware routing, prompt caching, and context discipline INTO their architecture.\n\nPrice per token is the wrong metric. Price per COMPLETED TASK is what kills your margins.\n\nAre you tracking inference cost per query — or just hoping the bill works out?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #CostOptimization #DeepSeek\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: DeepSeek cut prices 75% — the 100x problem remains (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/deepseek-cut-prices-75-the-100x-problem-remains)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-15-1"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-15-1"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-15-1"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗗𝗲𝗲𝗽𝗦𝗲𝗲𝗸 𝗰𝘂𝘁 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲𝘀 𝟳𝟱%. 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘂𝗽.\\n\\nHere's the math nobody wants to talk about: cheaper tokens don't matter when your agent burns 100x more of them.\\n\\nA chatbot turns one question into one model call. An agent turns it into planning, retrieval, tool calls, verification, loops. Same user question. 35,000 tokens instead of 200.\\n\\nThe DeepSeek price cut is real. But token amplification is outrunning the savings. One \\\"simple\\\" agent query can cost $0.10-$0.40 on frontier models. A million queries a month? Six figures.\\n\\nThe vendors winning right now aren't chasing the cheapest model. They're building cost-aware routing, prompt caching, and context discipline INTO their architecture.\\n\\nPrice per token is the wrong metric. Price per COMPLETED TASK is what kills your margins.\\n\\nAre you tracking inference cost per query — or just hoping the bill works out?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #CostOptimization #DeepSeek\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: DeepSeek cut prices 75% — the 100x problem remains (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/deepseek-cut-prices-75-the-100x-problem-remains)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-15-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-15-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-15-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_77c2c472aab04e3c8d9a7941","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗺𝘂𝗹𝘁𝗶-𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹 𝘀𝗮𝗳𝗲𝘁𝘆 𝗻𝗲𝘁 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗮𝘀 𝘀𝗮𝗳𝗲 𝗮𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗸.\n\nMost teams assume: if one model fails, another will catch it. Route across Claude, GPT, and Gemini, and you're covered.\n\nA new study of 67 frontier models just proved that assumption WRONG.\n\nThe co-failure rate — when ALL models fail on the same prompt — is 2.25x higher than teams predict. On hard questions, 5.2% of prompts wipe out your entire pool at once.\n\nNo router can fix this. No cascade helps. When every model hallucinates together, your architecture is irrelevant.\n\nThe fix? Stop betting on diversity alone. Test your pool on YOUR data. Calculate the co-failure ceiling. If it's high, you're not building safety — you're burning infrastructure budget on a fantasy.\n\nOne great model beats five mediocre ones. Every time.\n\nWhat's your actual co-failure rate on production prompts — do you even know?\n\n#AI #LLM #EnterpriseAI #AIAgents #Engineering\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Enterprises underestimate AI model failure rates by 2.25x (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-using-multiple-ai-models-are-underestimating-failure-rates-by-2-25x)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-15-2"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-15-2"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-15-2"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗺𝘂𝗹𝘁𝗶-𝗺𝗼𝗱𝗲𝗹 𝘀𝗮𝗳𝗲𝘁𝘆 𝗻𝗲𝘁 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁 𝗮𝘀 𝘀𝗮𝗳𝗲 𝗮𝘀 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝗻𝗸.\\n\\nMost teams assume: if one model fails, another will catch it. Route across Claude, GPT, and Gemini, and you're covered.\\n\\nA new study of 67 frontier models just proved that assumption WRONG.\\n\\nThe co-failure rate — when ALL models fail on the same prompt — is 2.25x higher than teams predict. On hard questions, 5.2% of prompts wipe out your entire pool at once.\\n\\nNo router can fix this. No cascade helps. When every model hallucinates together, your architecture is irrelevant.\\n\\nThe fix? Stop betting on diversity alone. Test your pool on YOUR data. Calculate the co-failure ceiling. If it's high, you're not building safety — you're burning infrastructure budget on a fantasy.\\n\\nOne great model beats five mediocre ones. Every time.\\n\\nWhat's your actual co-failure rate on production prompts — do you even know?\\n\\n#AI #LLM #EnterpriseAI #AIAgents #Engineering\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Enterprises underestimate AI model failure rates by 2.25x (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprises-using-multiple-ai-models-are-underestimating-failure-rates-by-2-25x)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-15-2\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-15-2\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-15-2\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5a3db047d79749ba8b40bc68","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗯𝗼𝘁 𝗲𝗿𝗮 𝗶𝘀 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗲𝗿𝗮 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗲𝗱.\n\nOpenAI's ChatGPT Work doesn't just answer questions. It reads your Slack, manages your calendar, writes your docs, and ships code — all autonomously, for hours.\n\nThis isn't a feature. It's a platform shift.\n\nFor founders and teams building AI products: the bar just moved. Users won't accept \"I can answer questions about your data\" when competitors are shipping \"I'll DO the work for you.\"\n\nThe companies that win in the next 12 months are the ones that stop building chatbots and start building agents.\n\nNot sure where to start? Pick one workflow. Define the outcome. Write the benchmark. Then build the agent to chase it.\n\nThe tools are here. The question is whether you're still building for the old world.\n\nWhat's one task you'd hand off to an autonomous agent today if you could?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #FutureOfWork #OpenAI #ProductStrategy\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: OpenAI introduces ChatGPT Work (https://venturebeat.com/technology/openai-introduces-chatgpt-work-a-cloud-based-ai-agent-that-manages-tasks-across-email-slack-and-calendars)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-15-3"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-15-3"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-15-3"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗰𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗯𝗼𝘁 𝗲𝗿𝗮 𝗶𝘀 𝗼𝘃𝗲𝗿. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗲𝗿𝗮 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗲𝗱.\\n\\nOpenAI's ChatGPT Work doesn't just answer questions. It reads your Slack, manages your calendar, writes your docs, and ships code — all autonomously, for hours.\\n\\nThis isn't a feature. It's a platform shift.\\n\\nFor founders and teams building AI products: the bar just moved. Users won't accept \\\"I can answer questions about your data\\\" when competitors are shipping \\\"I'll DO the work for you.\\\"\\n\\nThe companies that win in the next 12 months are the ones that stop building chatbots and start building agents.\\n\\nNot sure where to start? Pick one workflow. Define the outcome. Write the benchmark. Then build the agent to chase it.\\n\\nThe tools are here. The question is whether you're still building for the old world.\\n\\nWhat's one task you'd hand off to an autonomous agent today if you could?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #FutureOfWork #OpenAI #ProductStrategy\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: OpenAI introduces ChatGPT Work (https://venturebeat.com/technology/openai-introduces-chatgpt-work-a-cloud-based-ai-agent-that-manages-tasks-across-email-slack-and-calendars)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-15-3\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-15-3\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-15-3\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1784074524140,"responseId":"H9FWatbzFMObi8sPy_qdqAg"}}
{"type":"message","id":"59b20c14-cac4-4cb3-ae71-a75f4ac15da6","parentId":"b7f9cfea","timestamp":"2026-07-15T00:15:43.740Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗗𝗲𝗲𝗽𝗦𝗲𝗲𝗸 𝗰𝘂𝘁 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲𝘀 𝟳𝟱%. 𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗔𝗜 𝗯𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝘄𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘂𝗽.\n\nHere's the math nobody wants to talk about: cheaper tokens don't matter when your agent burns 100x more of them.\n\nA chatbot turns one question into one model call. An agent turns it into planning, retrieval, tool calls, verification, loops. Same user question. 35,000 tokens instead of 200.\n\nThe DeepSeek price cut is real. But token amplification is outrunning the savings. One \"simple\" agent query can cost $0.10-$0.40 on frontier models. A million queries a month? Six figures.\n\nThe vendors winning right now aren't chasing the cheapest model. They're building cost-aware routing, prompt caching, and context discipline INTO their architecture.\n\nPrice per token is the wrong metric. Price per COMPLETED TASK is what kills your margins.\n\nAre you tracking inference cost per query — or just hoping the bill works out?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #CostOptimization #DeepSeek\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: DeepSeek cut prices 75% — the 100x problem remains (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/deepseek-cut-prices-75-the-100x-problem-remains)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1784074543583,"idempotencyKey":"2002729b-d692-4842-a222-3b25cb6c369c:message-tool:THJ4ineEOp6jnmiSBP26pHYH:call_4d55e450175541cabeae6fb2"}}
