{"type":"message","id":"12ab9c92","parentId":"ede4609f","timestamp":"2026-07-16T00:15:56.201Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f5b8618bd39e45bf94c52950","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝟭𝗣𝗮𝘀𝘀𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗱 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲.\n\nNot because they wanted to. Because enterprises are bleeding token spend and nobody's watching.\n\nHere's the uncomfortable truth: a single engineering team running agentic workflows can burn through a prepaid token budget in weeks. Finance doesn't notice until the invoice arrives.\n\n1Password is betting this is the next FinOps crisis. Goldman Sachs estimates token consumption from AI agents will grow 24x by 2030.\n\nThe pattern is clear. We saw it with cloud infrastructure in the 2010s. Consumption-based pricing arrived, companies had no visibility, and an entire ecosystem of cost management tools emerged.\n\nAI tokens are next. The teams building visibility now are the ones who won't get surprised.\n\nAre you tracking token spend by team, user, and model — or just paying the bill when it comes?\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #CostManagement #FinOps #AIAgents\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: 1Password moves into AI cost management (https://venturebeat.com/security/1password-moves-into-ai-cost-management-betting-that-token-spend-is-the-next-enterprise-budget-crisis)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-16-1"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-16-1"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-16-1"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝟭𝗣𝗮𝘀𝘀𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗱 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲.\\n\\nNot because they wanted to. Because enterprises are bleeding token spend and nobody's watching.\\n\\nHere's the uncomfortable truth: a single engineering team running agentic workflows can burn through a prepaid token budget in weeks. Finance doesn't notice until the invoice arrives.\\n\\n1Password is betting this is the next FinOps crisis. Goldman Sachs estimates token consumption from AI agents will grow 24x by 2030.\\n\\nThe pattern is clear. We saw it with cloud infrastructure in the 2010s. Consumption-based pricing arrived, companies had no visibility, and an entire ecosystem of cost management tools emerged.\\n\\nAI tokens are next. The teams building visibility now are the ones who won't get surprised.\\n\\nAre you tracking token spend by team, user, and model — or just paying the bill when it comes?\\n\\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #CostManagement #FinOps #AIAgents\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: 1Password moves into AI cost management (https://venturebeat.com/security/1password-moves-into-ai-cost-management-betting-that-token-spend-is-the-next-enterprise-budget-crisis)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-16-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-16-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-16-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c0860af539534d85aee2527c","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗿𝗼𝘂𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝘀 𝗴𝘂𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴. 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗺𝗼𝗻𝗲𝘆.\n\nMost model routers are static. They look at the prompt, pick a model, and hope. They never see if the model actually succeeded.\n\nACRouter just changed the game. It's an open-source router that LEARNS from execution feedback. Every success, every failure, gets logged and used to improve the next decision.\n\nThe result? 2.6x cheaper than always-defaulting-to-Opus. Same accuracy.\n\nThis is the shift nobody's talking about. The winners in AI infrastructure aren't picking the \"best\" model. They're building systems that pick the RIGHT model for each task — and learn when they get it wrong.\n\nStatic routing is dead. Self-optimizing infrastructure is the new moat.\n\nIs your router learning from its mistakes — or just repeating them?\n\n#AI #LLM #AIAgents #CostOptimization #Engineering\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: ACRouter picks the smartest AI model per task (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/acrouter-picks-the-smartest-ai-model-per-task-beating-opus-only-setups-by-2-6x-on-cost)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-16-2"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-16-2"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-16-2"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗿𝗼𝘂𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝘀 𝗴𝘂𝗲𝘀𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗴. 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁'𝘀 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘆𝗼𝘂 𝗺𝗼𝗻𝗲𝘆.\\n\\nMost model routers are static. They look at the prompt, pick a model, and hope. They never see if the model actually succeeded.\\n\\nACRouter just changed the game. It's an open-source router that LEARNS from execution feedback. Every success, every failure, gets logged and used to improve the next decision.\\n\\nThe result? 2.6x cheaper than always-defaulting-to-Opus. Same accuracy.\\n\\nThis is the shift nobody's talking about. The winners in AI infrastructure aren't picking the \\\"best\\\" model. They're building systems that pick the RIGHT model for each task — and learn when they get it wrong.\\n\\nStatic routing is dead. Self-optimizing infrastructure is the new moat.\\n\\nIs your router learning from its mistakes — or just repeating them?\\n\\n#AI #LLM #AIAgents #CostOptimization #Engineering\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: ACRouter picks the smartest AI model per task (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/acrouter-picks-the-smartest-ai-model-per-task-beating-opus-only-setups-by-2-6x-on-cost)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-16-2\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-16-2\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-16-2\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b66cef3fd90042afb74619d4","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗖𝗮𝗻𝘃𝗮 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝟮𝟲𝟱 𝗺𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘂𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿 𝘁𝗼 𝗯𝘂𝗶𝗹𝗱 𝘄𝗲𝗯𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗲𝘀.\n\nNot developers. 265 million regular people. Including free accounts.\n\nThe \"vibe coding\" market hit $4.7B this year. Canva just entered it with a quarter-billion user head start.\n\nHere's why this matters for founders: the barrier to building software is collapsing. Your competitors can spin up a landing page in minutes. A prototype over lunch. An MVP by end of day.\n\nThe strategic question isn't \"can we build it?\" anymore. It's \"what's worth building?\"\n\nTools are becoming a commodity. Vision, taste, and understanding your customer? That's the edge.\n\nCanva's play is obvious: be the finishing layer for AI-generated code. Make it look good. Make it on-brand. Make it yours.\n\nWhat are you building with all these new tools — or are you still waiting for permission?\n\n#AI #NoCode #FutureOfWork #Startups #ProductStrategy\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Canva launches Code 2.0 (https://venturebeat.com/technology/canva-launches-code-2-0-offering-ai-website-building-to-every-user-including-free-accounts)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-16-3"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-16-3"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-16-3"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝗖𝗮𝗻𝘃𝗮 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗴𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝟮𝟲𝟱 𝗺𝗶𝗹𝗹𝗶𝗼𝗻 𝘂𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘀 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗼𝘄𝗲𝗿 𝘁𝗼 𝗯𝘂𝗶𝗹𝗱 𝘄𝗲𝗯𝘀𝗶𝘁𝗲𝘀.\\n\\nNot developers. 265 million regular people. Including free accounts.\\n\\nThe \\\"vibe coding\\\" market hit $4.7B this year. Canva just entered it with a quarter-billion user head start.\\n\\nHere's why this matters for founders: the barrier to building software is collapsing. Your competitors can spin up a landing page in minutes. A prototype over lunch. An MVP by end of day.\\n\\nThe strategic question isn't \\\"can we build it?\\\" anymore. It's \\\"what's worth building?\\\"\\n\\nTools are becoming a commodity. Vision, taste, and understanding your customer? That's the edge.\\n\\nCanva's play is obvious: be the finishing layer for AI-generated code. Make it look good. Make it on-brand. Make it yours.\\n\\nWhat are you building with all these new tools — or are you still waiting for permission?\\n\\n#AI #NoCode #FutureOfWork #Startups #ProductStrategy\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Canva launches Code 2.0 (https://venturebeat.com/technology/canva-launches-code-2-0-offering-ai-website-building-to-every-user-including-free-accounts)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-16-3\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-16-3\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-16-3\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1784160929015,"responseId":"ade8ecfe-f0bd-4ecf-a91a-c75bb1997d05"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f64cd6a-3877-44f9-8bb5-2e6e16bb1ca3","parentId":"12ab9c92","timestamp":"2026-07-16T00:15:56.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝟭𝗣𝗮𝘀𝘀𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗱 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗴𝗮𝗺𝗲.\n\nNot because they wanted to. Because enterprises are bleeding token spend and nobody's watching.\n\nHere's the uncomfortable truth: a single engineering team running agentic workflows can burn through a prepaid token budget in weeks. Finance doesn't notice until the invoice arrives.\n\n1Password is betting this is the next FinOps crisis. Goldman Sachs estimates token consumption from AI agents will grow 24x by 2030.\n\nThe pattern is clear. We saw it with cloud infrastructure in the 2010s. Consumption-based pricing arrived, companies had no visibility, and an entire ecosystem of cost management tools emerged.\n\nAI tokens are next. The teams building visibility now are the ones who won't get surprised.\n\nAre you tracking token spend by team, user, and model — or just paying the bill when it comes?\n\n#AI #EnterpriseAI #CostManagement #FinOps #AIAgents\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: 1Password moves into AI cost management (https://venturebeat.com/security/1password-moves-into-ai-cost-management-betting-that-token-spend-is-the-next-enterprise-budget-crisis)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1784160956523,"idempotencyKey":"9348da0e-63ab-4fdc-b130-5f175630655a:message-tool:GpRJI_7I0HXsFMAAhdyEpDJ3:call_f5b8618bd39e45bf94c52950"}}
