{"type":"message","id":"a8d0eed7","parentId":"827c0ed1","timestamp":"2026-07-16T14:46:20.548Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d96d0f9523d449eaa2220ba3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"UID=\"264468965\"\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\nPENDING_DIR=\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\"\nmkdir -p \"$PENDING_DIR\"\n\n# Save draft 1\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-14\nn: 1\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/openai-introduces-chatgpt-work-a-cloud-based-ai-agent-that-manages-tasks-across-email-slack-and-calendars\nsource_date: 2026-07-10\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗻𝗔𝗜 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗻𝗲𝗱 𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗼 𝗮 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗲𝗿.\n\nNot a chatbot. An actual autonomous agent that reads your Slack, manages your calendar, writes your docs, and ships code — all while you're at the beach.\n\nThis is the shift everyone's been waiting for. ChatGPT Work doesn't just answer questions. It takes a goal, breaks it into steps, and EXECUTES across your tools for hours.\n\nThe real signal? OpenAI is betting the IPO on agents being the future of work. Not chat. Not search. AGENTS.\n\nHere's what nobody's talking about: if your team isn't learning how to work with autonomous agents right now, you're already behind.\n\nThe tools are here. The question is whether you're still using them like chatbots — or like colleagues.\n\nWhat's the first task you'd hand off to an AI that actually works while you sleep?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Productivity #FutureOfWork #OpenAI\nDRAFT_EOF\n\necho \"SAVED: draft 1\"\n\n# Save draft 2\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-14\nn: 2\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprise-ai-is-entering-an-evaluation-gap-agents-are-gaining-autonomy-faster-than-companies-can-verify-them\nsource_date: 2026-07-10\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝟱𝟬% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗶𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\n\nThat's not a typo. Half the agents that looked fine in evals crashed when real customers used them.\n\nWhy? Because traditional tests check if something works ONCE. They don't check if it works EVERY time.\n\nThis is the evaluation gap. And it's the reason I've been saying: benchmark-first, agent-second.\n\nWrite the test before you write the agent. Make it pass 10 times in a row, not once. Build repeatability into the system from day one.\n\nMost teams are shipping agents like they ship prototypes — and then acting shocked when they break.\n\nA passing test isn't a working agent. It's a STARTING point.\n\nWhen's the last time you ran the same agent task 10 times and checked if the outcome was identical?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #TDD #EnterpriseAI\nDRAFT_EOF\n\necho \"SAVED: draft 2\"\n\n# Save draft 3\ncat > \"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\n---\ndate: 2026-07-14\nn: 3\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/spacexs-grok-4-5-launches-at-half-the-price-of-rivals-heres-why-that-could-rattle-anthropic-and-openai\nsource_date: 2026-07-09\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n𝗚𝗿𝗼𝗸 𝟰.𝟱 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗱𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗖𝗹𝗮𝘂𝗱𝗲 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗻𝗔𝗜.\n\nNot twice as smart. Just 90% cheaper per completed task.\n\nHere's what that actually means for you: if your AI strategy depends on ONE provider's pricing, you're overpaying. Period.\n\nThe model wars aren't about who's smartest anymore. They're about who delivers the most value per dollar. And that math is changing FAST.\n\nFor enterprises running agents that burn millions of tokens? This is the difference between \"maybe next quarter\" and \"ship it now.\"\n\nThe smartest teams aren't picking a winner. They're building stacks that can swap models when the economics shift.\n\nYour vendor lock-in is someone else's margin. Time to rethink that.\n\nHow many models is your team actually testing — or are you married to one API?\n\n#AI #LLM #EnterpriseAI #CostOptimization #Grok\nDRAFT_EOF\n\necho \"SAVED: draft 3\"\n\n# Mark brief as sent\ntouch \"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\"\necho \"BRIEF FLAG SET\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"UID=\\\"264468965\\\"\\nTODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d)\\nPENDING_DIR=\\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/$UID/pending\\\"\\nmkdir -p \\\"$PENDING_DIR\\\"\\n\\n# Save draft 1\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-1.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-14\\nn: 1\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/openai-introduces-chatgpt-work-a-cloud-based-ai-agent-that-manages-tasks-across-email-slack-and-calendars\\nsource_date: 2026-07-10\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗻𝗔𝗜 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗻𝗲𝗱 𝗖𝗵𝗮𝘁𝗚𝗣𝗧 𝗶𝗻𝘁𝗼 𝗮 𝘄𝗼𝗿𝗸𝗲𝗿.\\n\\nNot a chatbot. An actual autonomous agent that reads your Slack, manages your calendar, writes your docs, and ships code — all while you're at the beach.\\n\\nThis is the shift everyone's been waiting for. ChatGPT Work doesn't just answer questions. It takes a goal, breaks it into steps, and EXECUTES across your tools for hours.\\n\\nThe real signal? OpenAI is betting the IPO on agents being the future of work. Not chat. Not search. AGENTS.\\n\\nHere's what nobody's talking about: if your team isn't learning how to work with autonomous agents right now, you're already behind.\\n\\nThe tools are here. The question is whether you're still using them like chatbots — or like colleagues.\\n\\nWhat's the first task you'd hand off to an AI that actually works while you sleep?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Productivity #FutureOfWork #OpenAI\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\necho \\\"SAVED: draft 1\\\"\\n\\n# Save draft 2\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-2.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-14\\nn: 2\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprise-ai-is-entering-an-evaluation-gap-agents-are-gaining-autonomy-faster-than-companies-can-verify-them\\nsource_date: 2026-07-10\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝟱𝟬% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗹𝗹 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗶𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\\n\\nThat's not a typo. Half the agents that looked fine in evals crashed when real customers used them.\\n\\nWhy? Because traditional tests check if something works ONCE. They don't check if it works EVERY time.\\n\\nThis is the evaluation gap. And it's the reason I've been saying: benchmark-first, agent-second.\\n\\nWrite the test before you write the agent. Make it pass 10 times in a row, not once. Build repeatability into the system from day one.\\n\\nMost teams are shipping agents like they ship prototypes — and then acting shocked when they break.\\n\\nA passing test isn't a working agent. It's a STARTING point.\\n\\nWhen's the last time you ran the same agent task 10 times and checked if the outcome was identical?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #SoftwareEngineering #TDD #EnterpriseAI\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\necho \\\"SAVED: draft 2\\\"\\n\\n# Save draft 3\\ncat > \\\"$PENDING_DIR/${TODAY}-draft-3.md\\\" << 'DRAFT_EOF'\\n---\\ndate: 2026-07-14\\nn: 3\\npillar: Technology & AI innovations\\nsource: https://venturebeat.com/technology/spacexs-grok-4-5-launches-at-half-the-price-of-rivals-heres-why-that-could-rattle-anthropic-and-openai\\nsource_date: 2026-07-09\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n𝗚𝗿𝗼𝗸 𝟰.𝟱 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗱𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝘁 𝗵𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗽𝗿𝗶𝗰𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗖𝗹𝗮𝘂𝗱𝗲 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗻𝗔𝗜.\\n\\nNot twice as smart. Just 90% cheaper per completed task.\\n\\nHere's what that actually means for you: if your AI strategy depends on ONE provider's pricing, you're overpaying. Period.\\n\\nThe model wars aren't about who's smartest anymore. They're about who delivers the most value per dollar. And that math is changing FAST.\\n\\nFor enterprises running agents that burn millions of tokens? This is the difference between \\\"maybe next quarter\\\" and \\\"ship it now.\\\"\\n\\nThe smartest teams aren't picking a winner. They're building stacks that can swap models when the economics shift.\\n\\nYour vendor lock-in is someone else's margin. Time to rethink that.\\n\\nHow many models is your team actually testing — or are you married to one API?\\n\\n#AI #LLM #EnterpriseAI #CostOptimization #Grok\\nDRAFT_EOF\\n\\necho \\\"SAVED: draft 3\\\"\\n\\n# Mark brief as sent\\ntouch \\\"$PENDING_DIR/.brief-sent-$TODAY\\\"\\necho \\\"BRIEF FLAG SET\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783988081050,"responseId":"cn9VaoqSNvWT6dgP9d6WIQ"}}
