{"type":"compaction","id":"5b3987fb","parentId":"2accc910","timestamp":"2026-07-16T14:46:20.550Z","summary":"## Goal\n- Maintain a healthy LinkedIn posting cadence (2‑3 posts per day) for user **Andrii Bidochko** (UID 264468965).  \n- Ensure every LinkedIn post has a **unique, automatically generated image** (using the `image‑gen` skill).  \n- Keep **trend research up‑to‑date** (refresh proposals that are > 10 days old).  \n- Deliver a **daily brief** with up to three ready‑to‑publish drafts each morning.  \n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- Posts must not be published by the coach skill; publishing is done via `linkedin‑publish`.  \n- Follow the mandatory rules in `linkedin‑coach` (coach, not reporter; no step narration).  \n- Unique images must be 16:9, saved to the user’s `images` folder.  \n- User explicitly requested **unique images for each post**.  \n- (none)  \n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Added a plan to generate a unique image per post with `image‑gen`.  \n- [x] Updated `heartbeat-state.json` repeatedly to reflect current checks, cadence, and trend‑stale notes.  \n- [x] Generated the **July 14 daily brief** with three drafts (posts 1‑3) based on fresh VentureBeat articles and posted them to the user’s pending folder.  \n- [x] Sent the drafts to the user with “✅ Publish now / ✏️ Edit / ⏭️ Skip” buttons.  \n- [x] Tracked posting metrics: 17‑18 posts in the last 7 days (~2.4–2.6 /day).  \n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] Awaiting user action on the three July 14 drafts (publish, edit, or skip).  \n- [ ] Refresh stale trend proposals (last refreshed 2026‑07‑03).  \n- [ ] Generate unique images for upcoming posts after drafts are approved.  \n\n### Blocked\n- No current blockers; progress is waiting on user response.  \n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Use `image‑gen` for unique post images** – ensures each post looks fresh and avoids automation feel.  \n- **Flag trend proposals as stale** after > 10 days – prepares for a future trend‑refresh run.  \n- **Deliver drafts via the daily brief** rather than raw ideas – aligns with `linkedin‑coach` mandatory rules.  \n\n## Next Steps\n1. Wait for the user to **approve, edit, or skip** the July 14 drafts.  \n2. Once a draft is approved, trigger `image‑gen` to create its unique image and save it to the user’s `images` folder.  \n3. Run the **trend refresh** skill to update the “Trend Proposals” section in the content calendar.  \n4. Continue the heartbeat loop, updating `heartbeat-state.json` and notifying the user of cadence status.  \n5. Prepare the next day’s (July 15) daily brief with fresh drafts based on newly fetched news.  \n\n## Critical Context\n- **User ID / Paths**:  \n  - `/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/` (posts, pending, content‑calendar, profile, strategy)  \n  - `/data/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json` (lastChecks, notes)  \n- **July 14 Drafts** (saved in `pending/2026-07-14-draft-1.md` … `draft-3.md`):  \n  1. OpenAI ChatGPT Work – source: https://venturebeat.com/technology/openai‑introduces‑chatgpt‑work‑...  \n  2. Enterprise AI evaluation gap – source: https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/enterprise‑ai‑is‑entering‑an‑evaluation‑gap‑...  \n  3. SpaceX Grok 4.5 pricing – source: https://venturebeat.com/technology/spacexs‑grok‑4‑5‑launches‑at‑half‑the‑price‑...  \n- **Current cadence**: 17‑18 posts in the last 7 days, target 2‑3 per day met.  \n- **Trend status**: Last proposals dated 2026‑07‑03; flagged for refresh.  \n- **Image requirement**: 16:9 LinkedIn‑ready visuals saved to `images/` per post.  \n\n---\n\n**Turn Context (split turn):**\n\n## Original Request\nThe user triggered the “OpenClaw heartbeat poll”, effectively asking the assistant to prepare a daily LinkedIn brief – fetch the latest AI news, draft LinkedIn posts aligned with the user’s brand pillars, and make them ready for publishing.\n\n## Early Progress\n- **Brief‑sent check:** Confirmed no brief has been sent today and created a flag file for today’s brief.\n- **User & brand data:** Loaded LinkedIn UID 264468965, fetched OAuth token, display name (Andrii Bidochko), and extracted the user’s content pillars and tone from `profile.md`.\n- **News gathering:** Queried VentureBeat (AI category) and TechCrunch (AI category) and then retrieved three specific articles:\n  1. DeepSeek price cut & 100x problem.\n  2. Multi‑model failure‑rate study.\n  3. OpenAI’s ChatGPT Work release.\n- **Draft creation:** Generated three markdown drafts (one per article) with proper front‑matter (date, pillar, source, status) and content written in the user’s voice, saved them to `/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/pending/2026-07-15‑draft-*.md`.\n- **Flag update:** Touched the `.brief-sent-2026-07-15` flag file.\n\n## Context for Suffix\nThe assistant has just sent a friendly “Good morning, Andrii!” message informing the user that three LinkedIn post drafts are ready and inviting the user to tap ✅ to publish any immediately. The next steps will involve the user selecting drafts to publish or requesting edits. This message follows the successful creation and storage of the drafts.\n\n<read-files>\n/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-coach/SKILL.md\n/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-daily-brief/SKILL.md\n/data/workspace/skills/perplexity-research/SKILL.md\n/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md\n/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md\n/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/strategy.md\n</read-files>\n\n<modified-files>\n/data/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.json\n</modified-files>","firstKeptEntryId":"485dd97d","tokensBefore":7,"details":{"readFiles":["/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-coach/SKILL.md","/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-daily-brief/SKILL.md","/data/workspace/skills/perplexity-research/SKILL.md","/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/content-calendar.md","/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/profile.md","/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/strategy.md"],"modifiedFiles":["/data/workspace/memory/heartbeat-state.js