{"type":"message","id":"33768178","parentId":"d06997fd","timestamp":"2026-07-17T00:15:32.476Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3026b36d526d401a8e4ea410","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝟱𝟰% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗮𝗹𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱𝘆 𝗵𝗮𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘀𝗲𝗰𝘂𝗿𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗶𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁.\n\nAnd most still let agents share credentials.\n\nA new survey of 107 enterprises just exposed the agent security gap. The structural weakness isn't sophistication — it's identity.\n\nOnly 32% give every agent its own scoped, managed identity. The rest share API keys or human/service account credentials.\n\nThe consequence? When one agent is over-permissioned or compromised, the blast radius is your entire infrastructure. And forensics can't tell you which agent did what.\n\nThe correlation is stark: organizations with credential sharing anywhere in the fleet got hit at 63.5%. Those with fully scoped identity? 40.9%.\n\nThat's a 23-point difference.\n\nIf you're deploying agents without solving identity first, you're not shipping features. You're expanding your attack surface.\n\nDoes every agent in your stack have its own scoped identity — or are you hoping shared keys won't come back to bite you?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Security #EnterpriseAI #Identity\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: The agent security gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-agent-security-gap-54-of-enterprises-have-already-had-an-ai-agent-incident-and-most-still-let-agents-share-credentials)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-17-1"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-17-1"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-17-1"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝟱𝟰% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗮𝗹𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱𝘆 𝗵𝗮𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘀𝗲𝗰𝘂𝗿𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗶𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁.\\n\\nAnd most still let agents share credentials.\\n\\nA new survey of 107 enterprises just exposed the agent security gap. The structural weakness isn't sophistication — it's identity.\\n\\nOnly 32% give every agent its own scoped, managed identity. The rest share API keys or human/service account credentials.\\n\\nThe consequence? When one agent is over-permissioned or compromised, the blast radius is your entire infrastructure. And forensics can't tell you which agent did what.\\n\\nThe correlation is stark: organizations with credential sharing anywhere in the fleet got hit at 63.5%. Those with fully scoped identity? 40.9%.\\n\\nThat's a 23-point difference.\\n\\nIf you're deploying agents without solving identity first, you're not shipping features. You're expanding your attack surface.\\n\\nDoes every agent in your stack have its own scoped identity — or are you hoping shared keys won't come back to bite you?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Security #EnterpriseAI #Identity\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: The agent security gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-agent-security-gap-54-of-enterprises-have-already-had-an-ai-agent-incident-and-most-still-let-agents-share-credentials)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-17-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-17-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-17-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_967c264ee365479c8f10ba98","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝗘𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝘂𝘆𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗿𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗳𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗺𝗲𝗮𝘀𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗶𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝘀.\n\nNew research across 107 enterprises reveals a compute gap: heavy, fast-moving investment running ahead of the visibility needed to control it.\n\nThe numbers:\n• 83% report GPU utilization of 50% or less\n• Only 44% can rigorously track what their AI compute costs\n• 64% plan to switch or add infrastructure providers within 12 months\n\nMeanwhile, 45% are planning to evaluate AI-specialized clouds (CoreWeave, Lambda, Crusoe) — a category almost none of them use today.\n\nThis is the infrastructure version of the cloud cost crisis from the 2010s. Everyone's swiping the credit card. Few know the unit economics.\n\nThe teams that build visibility NOW — per-model cost, per-query spend, actual utilization metrics — are the ones who won't get surprised when the finance team finally asks \"where is this money going?\"\n\nCan you answer today what your AI compute cost per customer actually is?\n\n#AI #Infrastructure #EnterpriseAI #CostOptimization #FinOps\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: The AI compute gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-ai-compute-gap-enterprises-are-buying-infrastructure-faster-than-they-can-measure-what-it-costs)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-17-2"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-17-2"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-17-2"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝗘𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗯𝘂𝘆𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗿𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝗳𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗲𝗿 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝘆 𝗰𝗮𝗻 𝗺𝗲𝗮𝘀𝘂𝗿𝗲 𝘄𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗶𝘁 𝗰𝗼𝘀𝘁𝘀.\\n\\nNew research across 107 enterprises reveals a compute gap: heavy, fast-moving investment running ahead of the visibility needed to control it.\\n\\nThe numbers:\\n• 83% report GPU utilization of 50% or less\\n• Only 44% can rigorously track what their AI compute costs\\n• 64% plan to switch or add infrastructure providers within 12 months\\n\\nMeanwhile, 45% are planning to evaluate AI-specialized clouds (CoreWeave, Lambda, Crusoe) — a category almost none of them use today.\\n\\nThis is the infrastructure version of the cloud cost crisis from the 2010s. Everyone's swiping the credit card. Few know the unit economics.\\n\\nThe teams that build visibility NOW — per-model cost, per-query spend, actual utilization metrics — are the ones who won't get surprised when the finance team finally asks \\\"where is this money going?\\\"\\n\\nCan you answer today what your AI compute cost per customer actually is?\\n\\n#AI #Infrastructure #EnterpriseAI #CostOptimization #FinOps\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: The AI compute gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-ai-compute-gap-enterprises-are-buying-infrastructure-faster-than-they-can-measure-what-it-costs)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-17-2\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-17-2\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-17-2\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6b113c71c233427ab38100bc","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗛𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗲𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘀 — 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗮 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\n\nThe evaluation gap just got quantified. 157 enterprises surveyed. The result: a passing eval is not a working agent.\n\nThe problem isn't test coverage. It's reality alignment. The most-cited limitation (29%) is that evaluations don't match real-world outcomes.\n\nYet here's the paradox:\n• Only 5% fully trust automated evaluation\n• But 66% are already allowing or building toward zero-human-in-the-loop deployment\n\nTeams are removing the safety check at the exact moment they don't trust the test that would replace it.\n\nThe fix isn't more evals. It's evals that reflect what actually breaks in production. That means instrumenting real customer failures, feeding them back into your test suite, and measuring the gap between synthetic and real.\n\nAn evaluation suite that doesn't catch what breaks in production isn't QA. It's theater.\n\nWhen's the last time you traced a production failure back to your eval suite and fixed the test?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Engineering #EnterpriseAI #Quality\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: The agent evaluation gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-agent-evaluation-gap-enterprise-ai-organizations-have-a-reality-alignment-problem-not-a-coverage-problem-and-most-are-shipping-to-production-anyway)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-17-3"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-17-3"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-17-3"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗛𝗮𝗹𝗳 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘁𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗽𝗮𝘀𝘀𝗲𝗱 𝗲𝘃𝗮𝗹𝘀 — 𝘁𝗵𝗲𝗻 𝗳𝗮𝗶𝗹𝗲𝗱 𝗮 𝗰𝘂𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗺𝗲𝗿 𝗶𝗻 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\\n\\nThe evaluation gap just got quantified. 157 enterprises surveyed. The result: a passing eval is not a working agent.\\n\\nThe problem isn't test coverage. It's reality alignment. The most-cited limitation (29%) is that evaluations don't match real-world outcomes.\\n\\nYet here's the paradox:\\n• Only 5% fully trust automated evaluation\\n• But 66% are already allowing or building toward zero-human-in-the-loop deployment\\n\\nTeams are removing the safety check at the exact moment they don't trust the test that would replace it.\\n\\nThe fix isn't more evals. It's evals that reflect what actually breaks in production. That means instrumenting real customer failures, feeding them back into your test suite, and measuring the gap between synthetic and real.\\n\\nAn evaluation suite that doesn't catch what breaks in production isn't QA. It's theater.\\n\\nWhen's the last time you traced a production failure back to your eval suite and fixed the test?\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #Engineering #EnterpriseAI #Quality\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: The agent evaluation gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-agent-evaluation-gap-enterprise-ai-organizations-have-a-reality-alignment-problem-not-a-coverage-problem-and-most-are-shipping-to-production-anyway)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-17-3\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-17-3\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-17-3\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1784247305705,"responseId":"b6725c38-e096-450e-9ca6-ed5d514451c2"}}
{"type":"message","id":"97a4ed3e-2bc4-4380-b31b-f78dd2a14780","parentId":"33768178","timestamp":"2026-07-17T00:15:33.007Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝟱𝟰% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝗮𝗹𝗿𝗲𝗮𝗱𝘆 𝗵𝗮𝗱 𝗮𝗻 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝘀𝗲𝗰𝘂𝗿𝗶𝘁𝘆 𝗶𝗻𝗰𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁.\n\nAnd most still let agents share credentials.\n\nA new survey of 107 enterprises just exposed the agent security gap. The structural weakness isn't sophistication — it's identity.\n\nOnly 32% give every agent its own scoped, managed identity. The rest share API keys or human/service account credentials.\n\nThe consequence? When one agent is over-permissioned or compromised, the blast radius is your entire infrastructure. And forensics can't tell you which agent did what.\n\nThe correlation is stark: organizations with credential sharing anywhere in the fleet got hit at 63.5%. Those with fully scoped identity? 40.9%.\n\nThat's a 23-point difference.\n\nIf you're deploying agents without solving identity first, you're not shipping features. You're expanding your attack surface.\n\nDoes every agent in your stack have its own scoped identity — or are you hoping shared keys won't come back to bite you?\n\n#AI #AIAgents #Security #EnterpriseAI #Identity\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: The agent security gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-agent-security-gap-54-of-enterprises-have-already-had-an-ai-agent-incident-and-most-still-let-agents-share-credentials)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1784247332858,"idempotencyKey":"cb6d6a39-8a6e-41f4-a617-1e926d689310:message-tool:unFOpTP9Ij54oUovBMaSi6HT:call_3026b36d526d401a8e4ea410"}}
