.8 trillion parameters, fully open-source, benchmarking neck-and-neck with Claude and GPT at the top of the leaderboard.\\n\\nThe numbers:\\n• 3rd on GDPval-AA (real-world tasks across 44 occupations)\\n• 2nd on AA-Briefcase (long-horizon knowledge work)\\n• 91.2 on BrowseComp — state of the art for information seeking\\n\\nFull model weights drop July 27. API is live now at $3/M input tokens.\\n\\nHere's what matters: open-source has been trailing proprietary by 6+ months for years. That gap just closed. A Beijing startup built a model that competes with Anthropic and OpenAI — and they're giving it away.\\n\\nThe moats are getting harder to defend. If you're building your AI strategy around \\\"no one else can match our model,\\\" you might want to reconsider.\\n\\nWhat's your plan when frontier-class models become free?\\n\\n#AI #OpenSource #LLM #KimiK3 #EnterpriseAI\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: China's Moonshot AI releases Kimi K3 (https://venturebeat.com/technology/chinas-moonshot-ai-releases-kimi-k3-the-largest-open-source-model-ever-rivaling-top-u-s-systems)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-18-1\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-18-1\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-18-1\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c5a178cbdae14478a60aed22","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗶𝘀 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝗳𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝗳𝗲𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗶𝘁 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁.\n\nNew research across 101 enterprises reveals the context gap: 57% have had an AI agent produce a confident, wrong answer traced to bad context — wrong metrics, stale definitions, or missing documents.\n\nMore than half saw it happen more than once.\n\nThe infrastructure that feeds your agents is being built faster than it can be trusted. RAG is the default context source (38%), but provider-native retrieval (OpenAI file search, Google Vertex AI Search) now leads dedicated vector databases.\n\nThe fix is a governed semantic layer — shared business definitions that make context reliable. 58% are building one. Most aren't done yet.\n\nMeanwhile, your agents are answering confidently on thin air.\n\nThe question isn't \"is my model smart enough?\" It's \"does my agent actually have the right information?\"\n\nWhen's the last time you traced a confident wrong answer back to its source?\n\n#AI #RAG #EnterpriseAI #AIAgents #DataQuality\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: The AI context gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-ai-context-gap-enterprise-ai-organizations-have-a-trust-problem-not-a-retrieval-problem-and-most-are-still-building-the-fix)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-18-2"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-18-2"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-18-2"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 2/3 — Technology & AI innovations\\n\\n𝗬𝗼𝘂𝗿 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁 𝗶𝘀 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝗳𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗻𝘁. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗲𝘅𝘁 𝗳𝗲𝗲𝗱𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗶𝘁 𝗶𝘀𝗻'𝘁.\\n\\nNew research across 101 enterprises reveals the context gap: 57% have had an AI agent produce a confident, wrong answer traced to bad context — wrong metrics, stale definitions, or missing documents.\\n\\nMore than half saw it happen more than once.\\n\\nThe infrastructure that feeds your agents is being built faster than it can be trusted. RAG is the default context source (38%), but provider-native retrieval (OpenAI file search, Google Vertex AI Search) now leads dedicated vector databases.\\n\\nThe fix is a governed semantic layer — shared business definitions that make context reliable. 58% are building one. Most aren't done yet.\\n\\nMeanwhile, your agents are answering confidently on thin air.\\n\\nThe question isn't \\\"is my model smart enough?\\\" It's \\\"does my agent actually have the right information?\\\"\\n\\nWhen's the last time you traced a confident wrong answer back to its source?\\n\\n#AI #RAG #EnterpriseAI #AIAgents #DataQuality\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: The AI context gap (https://venturebeat.com/ai/the-ai-context-gap-enterprise-ai-organizations-have-a-trust-problem-not-a-retrieval-problem-and-most-are-still-building-the-fix)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-18-2\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-18-2\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-18-2\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b30027bf8382414d9e91676e","name":"message","arguments":{"action":"send","message":"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\n\n𝟴𝟱% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝗶𝗹𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀. 𝗢𝗻𝗹𝘆 𝟱% 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\n\nAmazon's AGI director just named the blocker: it's not capability. It's reliability.\n\nInside Amazon's lab, they call their agents \"interns\" — powerful but occasionally clueless. The framing matters. You don't manage interns with better algorithms. You manage them with better oversight.\n\nThe four dimensions of reliability:\n• Consistency — same input, same output\n• Robustness — handles edge cases\n• Predictability — you know when it will fail\n• Safety — failure doesn't break things\n\nOne customer's agent worked flawlessly for two months, then started reading wrong serial numbers. A subtle UI change triggered the failure. No one saw it coming.\n\nThe enterprises that escape pilot purgatory won't be the ones with the smartest agents. They'll be the ones with the best managers.\n\nStop asking \"can it do something impressive once?\" Start asking \"can it do it correctly a thousand times in a row?\"\n\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #Leadership #ProductManagement\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: Amazon AGI director on agent reliability (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/amazon-agi-director-says-ai-agent-reliability-not-capability-is-blocking-enterprise-deployment-at-vb-transform-2026)","presentation":{"blocks":[{"type":"buttons","buttons":[{"label":"✅ Publish now","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_approve_2026-07-18-3"},"style":"success"},{"label":"✏️ Edit first","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_edit_2026-07-18-3"}},{"label":"⏭️ Skip","action":{"type":"callback","value":"brief_skip_2026-07-18-3"},"style":"secondary"}]}]}},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"send\", \"message\": \"📝 Post 3/3 — Business & entrepreneurship insights\\n\\n𝟴𝟱% 𝗼𝗳 𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗲𝗿𝗽𝗿𝗶𝘀𝗲𝘀 𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗽𝗶𝗹𝗼𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗔𝗜 𝗮𝗴𝗲𝗻𝘁𝘀. 𝗢𝗻𝗹𝘆 𝟱% 𝗵𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽𝗽𝗲𝗱 𝘁𝗼 𝗽𝗿𝗼𝗱𝘂𝗰𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻.\\n\\nAmazon's AGI director just named the blocker: it's not capability. It's reliability.\\n\\nInside Amazon's lab, they call their agents \\\"interns\\\" — powerful but occasionally clueless. The framing matters. You don't manage interns with better algorithms. You manage them with better oversight.\\n\\nThe four dimensions of reliability:\\n• Consistency — same input, same output\\n• Robustness — handles edge cases\\n• Predictability — you know when it will fail\\n• Safety — failure doesn't break things\\n\\nOne customer's agent worked flawlessly for two months, then started reading wrong serial numbers. A subtle UI change triggered the failure. No one saw it coming.\\n\\nThe enterprises that escape pilot purgatory won't be the ones with the smartest agents. They'll be the ones with the best managers.\\n\\nStop asking \\\"can it do something impressive once?\\\" Start asking \\\"can it do it correctly a thousand times in a row?\\\"\\n\\n#AI #AIAgents #EnterpriseAI #Leadership #ProductManagement\\n\\n━━━━━━━━━━━\\nSource: Amazon AGI director on agent reliability (https://venturebeat.com/orchestration/amazon-agi-director-says-ai-agent-reliability-not-capability-is-blocking-enterprise-deployment-at-vb-transform-2026)\", \"presentation\": {\"blocks\": [{\"type\": \"buttons\", \"buttons\": [{\"label\": \"✅ Publish now\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_approve_2026-07-18-3\"}, \"style\": \"success\"}, {\"label\": \"✏️ Edit first\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_edit_2026-07-18-3\"}}, {\"label\": \"⏭️ Skip\", \"action\": {\"type\": \"callback\", \"value\": \"brief_skip_2026-07-18-3\"}, \"style\": \"secondary\"}]}]}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1784333758312,"responseId":"91164f28-3aca-48c1-b43f-04c15c4b85e7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"eb926fa2-5228-4df7-9917-eaed312cabe0","parentId":"4c2fccba","timestamp":"2026-07-18T00:16:22.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📝 Post 1/3 — Technology & AI innovations\n\n𝗢𝗽𝗲𝗻 𝘀𝗼𝘂𝗿𝗰𝗲 𝗷𝘂𝘀𝘁 𝗰𝗮𝘂𝗴𝗵𝘁 𝘂𝗽 𝘁𝗼 𝗰𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗲𝗱-𝘀𝗼𝘂𝗿𝗰𝗲.\n\nChina's Moonshot AI just released Kimi K3 — 2.8 trillion parameters, fully open-source, benchmarking neck-and-neck with Claude and GPT at the top of the leaderboard.\n\nThe numbers:\n• 3rd on GDPval-AA (real-world tasks across 44 occupations)\n• 2nd on AA-Briefcase (long-horizon knowledge work)\n• 91.2 on BrowseComp — state of the art for information seeking\n\nFull model weights drop July 27. API is live now at $3/M input tokens.\n\nHere's what matters: open-source has been trailing proprietary by 6+ months for years. That gap just closed. A Beijing startup built a model that competes with Anthropic and OpenAI — and they're giving it away.\n\nThe moats are getting harder to defend. If you're building your AI strategy around \"no one else can match our model,\" you might want to reconsider.\n\nWhat's your plan when frontier-class models become free?\n\n#AI #OpenSource #LLM #KimiK3 #EnterpriseAI\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━\nSource: China's Moonshot AI releases Kimi K3 (https://venturebeat.com/technology/chinas-moonshot-ai-releases-kimi-k3-the-largest-open-source-model-ever-rivaling-top-u-s-systems)"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1784333782444,"idempotencyKey":"0cb6af9e-11d8-472a-bb73-6315ce06e3ad:message-tool:QPqtqOv5034--pT4VJ3VJPwQ:call_1b67109228ec4b88bd289492"}}
